CONTEXT.md
     1→# toasty-codegen Component Context
     3→## Purpose
     4→Generates Rust code from the `#[derive(Model)]` procedural macro. This crate transforms user-defined structs into full-featured ORM models with query builders, CRUD operations, and relationship handling.
     5→
     6→## Key Responsibilities
     8→### Schema Parsing (`src/schema/`)
    15→### Code Expansion (`src/expand/`)
    25→## Common Change Patterns
    27→### Adding a New Model Attribute
    33→### Adding Query Methods
    39→### Supporting New Field Types
    45→## Generated Code Structure
    47→For a model `User`, codegen creates:
    48→```rust
    49→// Core implementations
    50→impl User { /* CRUD methods */ }
    51→impl Model for User { /* trait implementation */ }
    52→impl Relation for User { /* relationship support */ }
    53→impl IntoExpr<User> for User { /* expression conversion */ }
    54→impl IntoSelect for User { /* query conversion */ }
    55→
    56→// Builder structs
    57→struct UserQuery { /* query builder */ }
    58→struct UserCreate { /* insert builder */ }
    59→struct UserUpdate<'a> { /* update builder */ }
    60→struct UserUpdateQuery { /* update query builder */ }
    61→
    62→// Field accessors
    63→struct UserFields;
    64→impl UserFields { /* field path methods */ }
    65→
    66→// Relationship types
    67→struct Many, One, OptionOne, ManyField, OneField;
    68→```
    69→
    70→## Complete Attribute Support
    72→### Model-Level Attributes
    76→### Field-Level Attributes  
    83→### Relationship Attributes
    88→## Important Files
    90→- `lib.rs`: Macro entry point
    91→- `schema/model.rs`: Model parsing logic
    92→- `expand/model.rs`: Main expansion logic
    93→- `expand/util.rs`: Helper functions for code generation
    94→- `schema/ty.rs`: Type system mapping
    95→
    96→## Code Generation Principles
    98→1. **Fully Qualified Paths**: Always use `#toasty::Type` to avoid conflicts
    99→2. **Type Safety**: Generate strongly-typed builders and queries
   100→3. **Zero-Cost**: Generated code should have no runtime overhead
   101→4. **Discoverable API**: Methods should be intuitive and IDE-friendly
   102→
   103→## Key Patterns
   105→### Dynamic Model IDs
   114→### Query Builder Pattern
   123→### Relationship Expansion
   128→## Recent Changes Analysis
   130→From recent commits:
   131→- Switched from const Model::ID to method-based IDs
   132→- Reduced glob imports for clarity
   133→- Removed schema query generation (moved to runtime)
   134→- Simplified field accessor generation
   135→- Added support for more primitive types

